results.abstract: Article on late auto racing driver Jim Clark, adapted from Graham Gauld book Jim Clark Remembered; illus (L)

headline.main: Jim Clark: An Ordinary Human Being Who Found His Vocation

results.snippet: There is no archetypal race driver, and the next world champion could be that unemployed guy you see collecting his benefit--as in the case of Graham Hill--or else the cocky little kid down the road with the flashy Austin Healey and the jaunty walk...
results.lead_paragraph: There is no archetypal race driver, and the next world champion could be that unemployed guy you see collecting his benefit--as in the case of Graham Hill--or else the cocky little kid down the road with the flashy Austin Healey and the jaunty walk to match, like Jackie Stewart.
